---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Container, Section, Heading, Card, Prose } from '@/components';
import { now } from '@/config/pages';

---

<Layout meta={now}>
  <Section class="border-b border-stone-800/60">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <Heading level={1} class="mb-5">Now</Heading>
        <p class="text-xl text-stone-400 leading-relaxed">
          This is a <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">now page</a>. It’s a snapshot of what I’m doing, learning, and focused on right now.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-stone-500 italic">Last updated: April 10, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <Container>
      <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="lg:col-span-2">
          <Prose>
            <h3>Primary Focus</h3>
            <p>
              Right now, my main focus is leading as a <strong>Technical Director</strong>: helping teams make better technical decisions, building stronger engineering habits, and creating the space for people to do their best work. A lot of my week is spent in architecture conversations, API design reviews, and mentoring across product and platform.
            </p>

            <h3>What I'm Building Next</h3>
            <p>
              I am putting more energy into practical resources for senior developers and tech leads: clearer API design guidance, better standards discussions, and opinionated playbooks teams can use without guesswork. The goal is simple: less theory, more tools people can apply immediately.
            </p>

            <h3>Writing &amp; Speaking</h3>
            <p>
              I am continuing to write regularly and speak where I can add real value. I care most about topics that sit at the intersection of architecture, developer experience, and leadership, especially where teams are trying to move faster without sacrificing quality.
            </p>

            <h3>Recent Milestones</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Refined my publishing workflow to ship technical writing more consistently.</li>
              <li>Delivered talks and workshops focused on API design and team-level engineering practices.</li>
              <li>Continued mentoring engineers stepping into senior and leadership responsibilities.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>What Success Looks Like This Season</h3>
            <p>
              Helping teams ship with more clarity, giving developers practical patterns they can trust, and creating work that stays useful long after it is published.
            </p>
          </Prose>
        </div>

        <aside class="space-y-8">
          <Card>
            <Heading level={4} class="mb-4">Reading</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-stone-400">
              <li><span class="text-stone-100 font-medium">Team Topologies</span> by Matthew Skelton &amp; Manuel Pais</li>
              <li><span class="text-stone-100 font-medium">Staff Engineer</span> by Will Larson</li>
            </ul>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <Heading level={4} class="mb-4">Listening</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-stone-400">
              <li><span class="text-stone-100 font-medium">The Changelog</span></li>
              <li><span class="text-stone-100 font-medium">The Laravel Podcast</span></li>
            </ul>
          </Card>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>
</Layout>
